{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (signed, 0 blocking, 8 advisory). Triage + concrete decisions (remediating the valid advisories in implementation rather than churning the attested description):\n- [T8 f91b33 — the key one] A static per-step `model: sonnet` CANNOT honor an operator override because resolve_model precedence is step>workflow>cfg (a literal step model always wins). So the verifier Sonnet DEFAULT is applied via cfg-tuning at the review_plan() library entry — mirroring verify_completion (completion.py:200): `if cfg.model == DEFAULT_MODEL: cfg = replace(cfg, model=VERIFIER_DEFAULT_MODEL)`. This honors REBAR_LLM_MODEL exactly like verifier_cfg. The per-step `model:` editor field is a SEPARATE general capability that, when explicitly set on a step, wins via resolve_model — the two compose.\n- [fa622c/f87a8b] Concrete model id = claude-sonnet-4-6 (VERIFIER_DEFAULT_MODEL, promoted to config.py as a shared const so completion.py + plan_review share one source — no duplication).\n- [T8 f40b68] Editor model-select vocabulary = sizing.MODEL_LADDER ids (claude-haiku-4-5, claude-sonnet-4-6, claude-opus-4-8) + blank=inherit. Single source: sizing.MODEL_LADDER.\n- [E5 fb84a8] Add a test asserting the resolved verify model is Sonnet by default and the operator's model when REBAR_LLM_MODEL is set.\n- [G5 f45d8d/fd93d3] Thin vertical slice / de-risk order: (1) backend Sonnet pin + test (the load-bearing behavior) FIRST, then (2) editor model field + BPMN round-trip/back-compat tests (per-step model already round-trips via <rebar:Config>; legacy BPMN degrades gracefully), then (3) docs. WS2 is already a decomposed child of the epic."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782583017729240001,"uuid":"238d8bfd-ef4e-4bec-897d-5f7cd8c44345"}